cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.ET, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for the design of surface plasmon polaritons (SPP) films, which involves image processing and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of low-cost sample replacement algorithm in the training process, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep CNN for learning better models falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the ill-posed inverse problem, which falls under the sub-category of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Finally, the use of deep learning algorithms for optimization falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
